'''Phillipp Mwene''' (born 29 January 1994) is an Austrian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|full-back]] for {{German football updater|FSVMainz}} club [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].

==Club career==
=== VfB Stuttgart II ===
He made his first appearance for [[VfB Stuttgart II]] on 20 April 2013 in the [[3. Fußball-Liga|3. Liga]] against [[SV Wacker Burghausen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/index.php?id=505718&no_cache=1&action=showSchema&lang=D&liga=bl3m&saison=12&saisonl=2012&spieltag=34&spielid=1996&cHash=189a832c12ec6c1b34d6d30f42f5b122|title=Official match report: VfB Stuttgart II - Wacker Burghausen 0:0 (0:0)|publisher=[[German Football Association]]|accessdate=20 April 2013|date=20 April 2013}}</ref>

=== 1. FC Kaiserslautern ===
In 2016, Mwene signed with [[1. FC Kaiserslautern]]. In the 2017–18 season he was a consistent performer at [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] contributing 4 goals and 7 assists in 31 appearances while the club was relegated from the [[2. Bundesliga]].<ref name=mainz>{{cite news|title=Mwene wechselt nach Mainz|url=https://www.kicker.de/mwene-wechselt-nach-mainz-724465/artikel|access-date=23 May 2018|work=kicker Online|date=23 May 2018|language=German}}</ref>

=== Mainz 05 ===
In May 2018, [[Bundesliga]] side [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] announced Mwene would join the club on a free transfer from Kaiserslautern for the 2018–19 season.<ref name=mainz/>

=== PSV ===
On 27 May 2021, [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] announced Mwene would join the club on a [[Free transfer (association football)|free transfer]] from Mainz 05, effective from 1 July.<ref>{{cite web |date=1 June 2021 |title=PSV Contracteert Verdediger Phillipp Mwene |url=https://www.psv.nl/nieuwspagina/artikel/psv-contracteert-verdediger-phillipp-mwene.htm |accessdate=1 June 2021 |publisher=[[PSV Eindhoven]] |language=nl}}</ref>

=== Return to Mainz 05 ===
On 23 August 2023, Mwene returned to [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] with a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=1. FSV Mainz 05|url=https://www.mainz05.de/news/phillipp-mwene-kehrt-zu-mainz-05-zurueck|title=PHILLIPP MWENE KEHRT ZURÜCK|trans-title=PHILLIP MWENE RETURNS|date=23 August 2023|access-date=24 August 2023|language=de}}</ref>

==International career==
Mwene was born in [[Vienna]] and holds dual citizenship of Kenya and Austria. He is a youth international for Austria.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laola1.at/de/red/fussball/oefb-nationalteam/a-team/news/phillipp-mwene--das-ist-fodas-ueberraschungsmann-im-euro-kader/|title=Phillipp Mwene: Das ist Fodas Überraschungsmann|website=www.laola1.at}}</ref> He was called up to the preliminary [[Austria national football team|Austria]] squad for [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.oefb.at/oefb/News/Vorlaeufiger-OeFB-Kader-fuer-die-EURO-Vorbereitung-nominiert |title=Vorläufiger ÖFB-Kader für die EURO-Vorbereitung nominiert |trans-title=Provisional ÖFB squad nominated for Euro preparation |work=[[Austrian Football Association]] |date=19 May 2021 |access-date=19 May 2021 |language=de}}</ref>

He made his debut for the [[Austria national football team]] on 4 September 2021 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group F|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Israel national football team|Israel]], a 2–5 away loss. He started the game and played the whole match.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FIFA]]|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/mens/worldcup/qatar2022/qualifiers/uefa/match-center/400155670|title=Israel v Austria game report|date=4 September 2021}}</ref>

